article_title: White House's Last Tax And Budget Plan Arrives With A Whimper

article_metadata.author: Business in the Beltway

og.description: If the White House wanted to attract attention to its final budget, it could not have picked a worse day to make it public. With official Washington obsessed with today’s New Hampshire primary, the 2017 budget barely caused a ripple. But the budget does include some interesting ideas—a few of which might attract bipartisan support sometime in the future.
